result.execSummary:
Rachel A. Cox-Tuj was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Rachel A. Cox-Tuj was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 9:26 AM Cases called: 21CM347, 21CM371, 22CF511, 22CF603 & 22CM376. Prosecuting attorney Loralee Clark in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Rachel A. Cox-Tuj in court, in custody.  Attorney Robert Allen Thorson not in court had car trouble. New date set.

9:37 AM 21CM347, 21CM371, 22CF511, 22CF609 & 22CM376. Prosecuting attorney Tiffany M. Winter in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Rachel A. Cox-Tuj in court, in custody.  Attorney Robert Allen Thorson in court for Rachel A. Cox-Tuj.
 
22CF511 is an Extradition. Defense has reviewed the fugitive complaint. Defendant would like to waive the Extradition. Defendant signs Waiver. 

Defense requests a quick turn around to possibly resolve other cases before Defendant is transported to Stearns County Minnesota.
Hearing scheduled for July 7, 2022 at 09:30 am.

(9:34 AM cases 21CM347, 21CM371, 22CM376, 22CF511, 22CF603 called.) Prosecuting attorney Afton Brianna Lewis in court for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant Rachel A. Cox-Tuj in court, in custody.  Attorney Robert Allen Thorson in court for Rachel A. Cox-Tuj.
Attorney Thorson advises has an offer but isn't inclusive of everything.
Parties address case 22CF511 and Attorney Thorson will reach out to Minnesota.
Court advises will set a new hearing for the extradition paperwork to be signed in court.
Hearing scheduled for July 5, 2022 at 09:30 am.

(9:43 AM cases 21CM347, 21CM371, 22CM376, 22CF511 called.) All parties and court personnel appear via Zoom. 
Prosecuting attorney Trenton Piltz in court for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant Rachel A. Cox-Tuj appeared by phone. Attorney Robert Allen Thorson in court for Rachel A. Cox-Tuj. 
Attorney Thorson advises has offer from the State and needs more time.
Court notes oldest file goes back a year and will not allow any further adjournments after this one.
Parties understand if there is no agreement at the next hearing, cases will need to be scheduled for trial.
Hearing scheduled for June 30, 2022 at 09:30 am.
No additional conditions set by the court.
